The Employee Management System is a simple Python project that helps manage employee records using a MySQL database. It is a console-based application where users can perform basic operations like adding, removing, promoting, and displaying employee details.

The system is connected to a MySQL database, which ensures that employee data is stored permanently and can be easily managed. It demonstrates the use of CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete) in Python with MySQL, making it a great project for beginners to understand database connectivity and basic management systems.

This project is useful for learning:
Python, database, connection with MySQL

Writing SQL queries in Python

Implementing real-world operations (Add, Remove, Update, Display)

Designing simple management systems.
